column1: OMAP-34: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Human Esophagus with CODEX

column2: Jeffrey Reina; Diana Mahdessian; Emma Lundberg

column24: rationale
Defines cornulin, a marker of esophageal squamous epithelial differentiation and stress response, enriched in suprabasal layers.
Defines adherens junctions connecting squamous epithelial cells; supports cell segmentation by marking membranes.
Defines heat shock protein 27, upregulated under stress; marks epithelial stress response.
A cytokine released by stressed/damaged epithelial cells; contributes to immune recruitment in esophagus.
Defines involucrin, a squamous epithelial differentiation marker in suprabasal layers.
Defines non-keratinized stratified squamous epithelial cells of esophagus; basal/suprabasal marker.
Defines keratin induced by injury/stress (hyperplasia, wound repair); marks abnormal epithelial responses.
Defines matrix metalloproteinase 1, expressed in stressed epithelial cells and stroma; remodels extracellular matrix.
Defines mucin 1 in glandular/ductal epithelial cells; associated with metaplastic or protective mucosa.
Defines DNA damage response and apoptosis regulation; upregulated in stress and carcinogenesis.
Defines periostin, secreted by fibroblasts; marks activated stroma and fibrosis in esophagus.
Defines periplakin, a structural component of desmosomes; essential for epithelial barrier integrity.
Defines tumor suppressor gene product; loss associated with carcinogenesis and epithelial transformation.
Defines α-SMA, smooth muscle and myofibroblast marker; helps annotate muscularis and activated fibroblasts.
Defines apoptosis regulator; overexpressed in stressed/dysplastic epithelia.
Defines helper T cells infiltrating esophageal mucosa.
Defines cytotoxic T cells infiltrating epithelium and lamina propria.
Defines blood endothelial cells; labels esophageal vasculature.
Defines vascular endothelial and stromal progenitor cells; vasculature and fibroblastic niche.
Defines pan-leukocyte marker; essential for immune cell annotation.
Defines macrophages and monocytes infiltrating the esophagus.
Defines regulatory T cells in mucosal immunity and tolerance.
Defines hypoxia-inducible factor; marks epithelial/stromal response to hypoxia and stress.
Defines proliferating epithelial and immune cells; proliferation marker.
Defines basal epithelial cells of stratified squamous mucosa.
Defines basal squamous epithelial cells; co-expressed with KRT14.
Defines inhibitory receptor on T cells; immune checkpoint in inflamed or dysplastic mucosa.
Defines immune checkpoint ligand on epithelial and immune cells; relevant for immune escape.
Defines transcription factor regulating basal epithelial progenitors; overexpressed in squamous cell carcinoma.
Defines basal and progenitor epithelial cells; essential for stratified epithelium maintenance.
Defines stromal fibroblasts and mesenchymal cells of esophagus.
